description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultant in Palliative Medicine &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;St Ann’s Hospice&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Heald Green&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Discover a place where knowledge, expertise and passion combine, St Ann’s Hospice is proud to be one of the largest adult hospices outside London, encompassing the localities of Manchester, Salford, Stockport, Trafford, Wigan, Bolton and Eastern Cheshire and serving a population of approximately 1.25 million. The hospice was founded in 1971, initially at St Ann&#39;s Hospice Heald Green, and has been caring for patients with life-limiting illnesses and their families ever since.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As we approach our 50th anniversary, the hospice has ambitious plans to ensure that we can continue to deliver high quality services to all of those that need them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today, our three sites provide a complete range of care for both patients and their families. This care is based on the simple idea that a person who has a life-limiting illness or is dying is still very much a living person, with unique physical, emotional, social and spiritual needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to the creation of a new post, we are looking to appoint a &lt;strong&gt;Consultant in Palliative Medicine, based at St Ann’s Hospice, Heald Green. &lt;/strong&gt;This is an exciting role and has been created to support the development of the seven day consultant service. There is a well-established consultant team within the hospice, working with an experienced MDT. You will also be involved with a community session within Trafford and the hospice is also host to specialty trainees and other training grades.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The core values of St Ann’s Hospice are at the heart of what we do and we expect all staff to work in a way that demonstrates they are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compassionate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Restpectful and&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;inclusive&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Information&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Further information regarding the hospice values are in the job description along with further background information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will agree to live within 10 miles or 30 minutes commute of the St Ann’s Hospice site and be a car owner with a full driving licence&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although this post is based at St Ann’s Hospice, you will be employed by Salford Royal, part of the Northern Care Alliance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salford Care Organisation is part of the Northern Care Alliance, one of the largest NHS organisations in the country. Based at Salford Royal NHS Foundation Trust, we believe in saving and improving lives and our expert and highly specialist teams deliver pioneering services and cutting-edge treatments that create exceptional outcomes for patients. We’re passionate about delivering quality integrated health and social care to our local community. If you share our vision, take your place with us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that interviews are taking place on 26th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr David Waterman, Hospice Medical Director dwaterman@sah.org.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alison Roberts, Consultant in Palliative Medicine aroberts@sah.org.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
